edu.rit.pj2.vbl

Class BitSet64Vbl.MaxSize

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.BitSet64
      • edu.rit.pj2.vbl.BitSet64Vbl
        • edu.rit.pj2.vbl.BitSet64Vbl.MaxSize
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable, Vbl, Cloneable
    Enclosing class:
    BitSet64Vbl

    public static class BitSet64Vbl.MaxSize
extends BitSet64Vbl
    Class BitSet64Vbl.MaxSize provides a reduction variable for a set of integers from 0 to 63, where the reduction operation is to keep the set with the largest size. The set elements are stored in a bitmap representation.

      • reduce

        public void reduce(Vbl vbl)
        Reduce the given shared variable into this shared variable. The two variables are combined together, and the result is stored in this shared variable. The reduce() method does not need to be multiple thread safe (thread synchronization is handled by the caller).

        The BitSet64Vbl.MaxSize class's reduce() method changes this set to the given set if the given set's size is larger.

        Specified by:
        reduce in interface Vbl
        Overrides:
        reduce in class BitSet64Vbl
        Parameters:
        vbl - Shared variable.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if the class of vbl is not compatible with the class of this shared variable.
